
[1]sophism

   SOPH'ISM, n. [L. sophisma.] A specious but fallacious argument;
   asubtilty in reasoning; an argument that is not supported by sound
   reasoning , or in which the inference is not justly deduced from the
   premises. When a false argument puts on the appearance of a true one,
   then it is properly called a sophism or fallacy.
